                           // Most important and most used <string.h> functions in C


1. String Length
strlen(s) → Get length of a string (excluding \0).

2. Copying
strcpy(dest, src) → Copy string.

strncpy(dest, src, n) → Copy with a limit.

memcpy(dest, src, n) → Copy raw memory.

memmove(dest, src, n) → Copy memory safely when overlap is possible.

3. Concatenation
strcat(dest, src) → Append string.

strncat(dest, src, n) → Append with limit.

4. Comparison
strcmp(s1, s2) → Compare strings.

strncmp(s1, s2, n) → Compare up to n chars.

memcmp(ptr1, ptr2, n) → Compare memory.

5. Search
strchr(s, c) → Find first occurrence of a char.

strrchr(s, c) → Find last occurrence of a char.

strstr(haystack, needle) → Find substring.

memchr(ptr, c, n) → Find byte in memory.

6. Tokenizing
strtok(s, delim) → Split string into tokens.

7. Memory Setting
memset(ptr, c, n) → Fill memory with a value.

